						<summary>

						<p>On a stone by the side of the Vīrabhadra temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1544 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14[66], Krōdhin, Kārtika śu. 12,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1544 A.D., October 27 (Monday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the remission of <hi rend="italic">maṅgali-pannu, sidhāyam</hi> etc., in Miḍutūru on the barbers in Pullēṭi-māgāṇi included in Gutti-durgam, by Alluḍu Rāmarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
